To set the language in your server you must first make sure your server has "Community" enabled, goto the **"Enable Community"** tab in server settings to get started.

Once community is enabled, under **"Community" > "Overview"** you can set your **"Server Primary Language"** to your desired language.

*Only the languages below are supported, if your server language is not supported it will default to english.*

column2:
• Your guild's id is used to store all settings so we can link the data to your guild.
• The custom prefix in your server is stored
• If you add a server address, that ip/hostname and port are stored
• If you setup a status channel the channel id, status message id and stutus channel type are stored
• If you add an invite to server discovery the invite will be stored, also whether you have discovery enabled will also be stored
• If you disable any commands the list of disabled commands is stored
Why do we store your information?

• We store your custom prefix in order for you to run commands with the prefix you specifiy
• Your server address and port are used in order to get information from your minecraft server without the information being typed-in every time
• Status channel id's are stored so we know where to send status messages and the status message id and type is stored so we know what message to update and how to display your server information
• Your server discovery settings are stored so we know if we should display your server on discovery and the discord invite to display
• Disabled commands are stored so we know what commands to deny users from running in your guild
• You can view all of your settings using the `{0}settings` command\n• Only the developer and high level admins of the bot can view your data
You can delete all of your data by either, removing the bot from your discord server. Or by running `{0}resetsettings` which will set all of your settings to their default values.
If you would like information or help on a specific matter [join our support server](https://discord.gg/uqVp2XzUP8)
Remove all of your settings and reset them to default
All of your settings have been removed and reset to their default values.

column2: A walkthrough on how to setup up the server
column3: Une procédure pas à pas pour la configuration du serveur

column2:
Let's get your server setup! First there is a few commands that you are going to have to run.

**Customizing your prefix**
You can give your server a custom prefix by running `{0}prefix <prefix>`!

**Connecting your server**
Set the server address for this guild by running `{0}setaddress <server address>`, for example `{0}setaddress mc.hypixel.net:25565`.

If your server uses the default port `25565` then you do not have to add the `:25565` onto the end, otherwise you should.

**Tweaking the address**
If you ever want to change the port at anytime you can use `{0}setport <port>` to change the port used by the bot without having to write out the server ip.

You can also do the same for the server ip by doing `{0}setip <server ip>` without having to write out the server port.

*(You can use the arrows below to flick between pages)*

You can check the settings for your server at anytime by running `{0}settings`, this will show you a list of all the settings stored about your server.

**What are these settings used for?**
Many commands use these settings to reduce the amount of typing needed when wanting to see information about your server.

You can test some of these commands that use your server settings:
• `{0}status`
• `{0}players`
• `{0}mods`
• `{0}plugins`

**Advanced settings**
Turn to the next page for a guide on more advanced features and settings!

**Our privacy policy**
If you would like to find out what we do with your data in detail then you can read our privacy policy by running `{0}policy`

Here is a guide on more advanced settings and features of the bot.

**Server querying**
Some servers may have the `query.port` setting in their `server.properties` file set to a different port compared to the port used to connect to the server.
This port is needed in order to get details such as **players**, **mods** and **plugins** from the server.
You must also ensure that `enable-query=true` is set in the `server.properties` file.

By default the query port is set to `-1` and will instead use the port used to connect to the server, run `{0}queryport <port>` to change the query port.

**Status channels**
A status channel is where live updates about your server will be posted.
You can set your status channel by doing `{0}setstatuschannel <channel>`, updates will be sent to this channel every 60 seconds.

You can change the look and way that this information is displayed by running `{0}setstatuschannel display <type>`.
The `panel` types will post a single message that is constantly updated with server information.

Server discovery allows other people from other servers, that have this bot, to find your server and for you to find their server!

You can view the list of these servers by doing `{0}discover`.

If you would like to add your server to the discovery list then you can run `{0}setserverdiscovery display on` and your server should appear in the list!
Your server will appear in **bold** with the :diamond_shape_with_a_dot_inside: symbol next to it.

You can also attach a discord invite next to your server address so that people can join your discord server, add the invite by running `{0}setserverdiscovery invite <invite>`. The invite must be a full discord invite link.

You can at anytime remove your server from the discovery list or remove your discord invite by running the commands as such:
• `{0}setserverdiscovery display off`
• `{0}setserverdiscovery invite remove`.

Here are some additional features you can use!

**Disabling commands**
If you would like to disable certain commands within your server then you can! To disable a command you can do `{0}disabled add <command>`, this will add the command to a list of disabled commands for your server. For example `{0}disabled add createmotd` will disable the `{0}createmotd` command.

If you ever want to re-enable a command then run `{0}disabled remove <command>` this will remove the command from the disabled list.
You can also re-enable all disabled commands by running `{0}disabled removeall`.

**Removing bot messages**
If you want to clean messages specifically from this bot from a channel then you can use the `{0}clear` command.

To remove a certain number of messages you can use `{0}clear count <number>`.

If you would like to clear messages posted after a certain date and time you can use `{0}clear after <date>`, you should represent dates as yyyy/mm/dd, 'today', 'yesterday' and 'this week' also work.

You can also just remove the previous message by running `{0}clear previous`
